This set of flags attempts to translate the iconography of the flag of Rhode Island into the realm of knowledge (specifically the acquiring, employing, sharing and spreading of it). It does so by combing a variety of fairly known symbols along with those included in the flag of Rhode Island. The latter consists of a gold anchor which is considered to be a symbol of hope (which is also the state\'92s motto). The presence of blue possibly refers to Rhode Island being known as the Ocean State. The displayed series of designs seems to take this symbolism further by transforming it into a narrative while always intrinsically belonging to the symbolism associated with Rhode Island. Similarly, the color scheme that runs through the series parallels that of the flag of the state and consists of white, gold and a dark yet saturated blue. \
